// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - GhostWidow 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro2 Text :
"P2697761423" "Normally I would kill you where you stand.  However, I doubt that it's a coincidence that you've shown up at the same time as I, especially considering the state of your precious Longbow agents.  Doc Quantum seems to be playing a dangerous game.  And I plan to put an end to his insolence!"
// Answer Text :
"P3224681499" "What have you done to the Longbow Operatives, Ghost Widow?"
// Page WhatLongbow Text :
"P4174746752" "We have little time to chitchat, worm.  Neither I nor Arachnos have done anything to your people.  This is Doc Quantum's doing, through and through."
// Answer Text :
"P3599111507" "Doc Quantum?  He's the one who clued me in on your actions."
// Page DocCluedIn Text :
"P2522348289" "Ahhhh... Of course... He set us up.  Even you, {HeroName}. We're here to pick up his Probability Generator he has graciously given to Arachnos.  Supposedly this device would have allowed us to alter possible outcomes.  But clearly it's a trap.  So now my mission changes.  Rather than take it, on behalf of Arachnos I'll destroy it - AND HIM WITH IT!"
// Answer Text :
"P396538890" "Show me this Generator at once and perhaps I'll go light on you."
// Page ShowGenerator Text :
"P2594615612" "YOU DARE THREATEN ME!?  No, {HeroName}, you have made a grave mistake.  A grave mistake, indeed.  Were it not for the fact that I am weakened, I would smite you where you stand.  However..."
// Answer Text :
"P3497482614" "However what?  Speak quickly, Widow, for my patience wears thin."
// Page HoweverRemark Text :
"P2742632421" "Oh, we wouldn't want that, now would we?  To have a lummox like you... upset? Heh heh... Yes, that would terrible wouldn't it?<br><br> I will show you the generator, but only because my anger towards Doc Quantum is greater than my annoyance with your pathetic threats."
// Answer Text :
"P1575566488" "When the Longbow operatives are freed, then we'll pick this back up."
// Page FreeLongbow Text :
"P672211196" "Oh, no, I don't think we will.  What's going to happen is that you're going to do all the work.  And when you've finished playing the goody-two-shoes hero that you are... Well, then you'll learn what it means to raise my ire.<br><br>Enough of this talk!  Let us move!"
// Answer Text :
"P3984880386" "I'm watching you, Widow.  Remember that."
// Page FirstAmbush Text :
"P3603275402" "Doc Quantum has crossed the line!  I care not a whit for your people being under his sway, but he will NOT touch Arachnos! Perhaps I've underestimated his determination to be killed by my hand."
// Answer Text :
"P1729289259" "Not if I don't do it first."
// Page WidowWhat Text :
"P813566759" "What did you just say?"
// Answer Text :
"P3415895936" "You heard me, Widow."
// Page Disgrace Text :
"P1651132426" "<color orange>Swift Cut clenches her hand, looking downward, tears appearing in her eyes.</color><br><br>I'm...I'm <i>not</i> a disgrace to my family...I'm NOT! <br><br>You understand, don't you {HeroName}?! About what must be done? To salvage everything from nothing?!"
// Answer Text :
"P3172180782" "...is this going to take a while? We're on a schedule here."
// Page Schedule Text :
"P2617139913" "Do...do you not even care {HeroName}? About this?"
// Answer Text :
"P2241975110" "Look, you hired me to protect you - and I am. I'm not interested in extra baggage."
// Page Baggage Text :
"P4237941616" "<color orange>Swift Cut sighs, gathering herself.</color><br><br>...very well. You're right. Let's get moving."
// Answer Text :
"P4168097617" "It's about time. Let's go!"
// Page Determined Text :
"P1054447141" "I'm determined to get through this {HeroName}. No matter what."
// Answer Text :
"P4173687746" "Good. Let's keep moving."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DocQuantum 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3201034955" "I shall make this quick, my friends. The device in which I have controlled the thoughts of your fellow allies is but a ruse to draw you out.  The real Generator can be found a short ways away.<br><br>However, there will be a minor snag in your plans to stop the generator."
// Answer Text :
"P1136714487" "Talk fast before I put an end to this."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P49028173" "Now, now, {HeroName}.  Try as you might, you wouldn't be able to harm me to begin with.  This is a projection based off of the possibility that I could be here. However, in truth, I am not.  Now... Do you wish to hear how to save the precious minds of those you claim to care about?"
// Answer Text :
"P1080289460" "Go on, Quantum."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P3112432512" "I have placed a remote deactivator within an unassuming container a little ways up.  Use that device and you'll stop my machine from controlling the minds of millions of residents within Paragon City and all of the Rogue Isles.  And this is where I apply the 'but'."
// Answer Text :
"P1252721555" "What are you planning, Quantum?"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P4130203831" "Well, you see... If you turn off my device, all of those already controlled will experience a bad side effect.  Namely, their brains will explode within their very skulls.<br><br>Thus... If you wish to save the city, you'll need to cause the deaths of countless operatives.  Innocents, I believe is the word for them, yes?"
// Answer Text :
"P2747292314" "You're sick, Quantum!  When I'm done... I'll be sure to give you some special medicine."
// Page Luck Text :
"P3634101656" "Yes, and I believe you would, too."
// Answer Text :
"P121056865" "Quan-"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3441803894" "Even though Quantum has crossed the line in the past, it's entirely possible that this is his attempt to atone for his past crimes.  Even if this is just some game between fellow Villains, it's best not to look a gift ghost in the mouth.<br><br>Finding Ghost Widow unawares is an opportunity you can't pass up.  And seeing that no other hero will be getting in the way, you can bring justice to her once and for all."
// AcceptString :
"P764687247" "Find Ghost Widow and take her out once and for all."
// SendOffString :
"P3604277200" "You make note of the location Quantum provided you and make your way there."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P583435603" "Find and eliminate the nefarious Ghost Widow!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1697386993" "No one has any patience in this town anymore."
// TaskTitle :
"P3134902679" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The End Justifies the Means</color></span></scale></font>"
// TaskSubTitle :
"P2380894755" "<span align=center><color orange><i>Vigilante Morality Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P553279849" "This is the place that Quantum told you that you would find Ghost Widow.  However, it seems that Longbow was one step ahead of you.  Good work, guys!"
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P2273623169" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>The End Justifies the Means</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Morality Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You've saved the citizens of Paragon City at the cost of having to personally be the one to terminate the lives of countless individuals who swore to protect the people.  But they knew what they were getting into when they signed on.<br><br>As sad as it may be, they died protecting everyone.  It's a good thing you were there, or it might have been a much larger death toll."
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P856364347" ""

